//@version=5
// Fib Strategy — VISUAL v4.1 (evidence-based defaults). Draws ONLY the latest setup:
//   yellow = entry   green = target   red dashed = stop   solid red steps = live trailing stop
//
// ---- CHANGELOG v4.1 (offline backtest #2: 10 US large-caps, one per GICS
//      sector - AAPL JPM JNJ XOM PG HD CAT NEE DIS AMT - real daily OHLCV
//      Feb-2013..Feb-2018, Python port of this exact logic, 0.05%/side
//      commission + 2-tick slippage on stop fills) -----------------------------
//  GOAL of this revision: maximize WIN RATE (>= 75% required) while keeping
//  the strategy profitable. That demands the opposite exit geometry from
//  v3/v4: enter a DEEP pullback, take profit QUICKLY, park a WIDE stop.
//  NEW DEFAULT = "HIGH-WIN PROFILE" (5 dev tickers -> 5 untouched holdout):
//    prd=5, entryFib=0.55, tgtFib=0.786, stopBuf=0.8, trailStop=OFF,
//    volume filter OFF, maxHold=80:
//      dev      win 84.9%  PF 2.13
//      holdout  win 81.4%  PF 1.55
//      all 10   win 83.0%  PF 1.79, avg +0.13R, n=188, max losing streak 2
//      9/10 tickers >= ~74% win rate; exits: 154 targets / 28 stops / 6 time
//  ROBUSTNESS: every neighboring combo (entry 0.5-0.618, tgt 0.7-0.786,
//  stopBuf 0.65-0.8, maxHold 60-80) also passed win>=75% AND PF>=1 on BOTH
//  splits - a plateau, not a lucky spike.
//  THE TRADE-OFF (read this): the high win rate is bought with reward:risk
//  ~0.17 - winners are small (+0.17R) and the rare stop-out costs a full -1R
//  (~8 wins). PF 1.79 is real, but sizing discipline matters: with the wide
//  stop, risk-based sizing (ON by default) keeps each stop-out at ~1% equity.
//  The v3/v4 "EXPECTANCY PROFILE" (bigger R, ~40% win, PF ~2.0-2.6) is still
//  in here - set prd=8, entryFib=0.382, tgtFib=1.0, stopBuf=0.05,
//  trailStop=ON, volume filter ON (1.3x), maxHold=60.
//  KNOWN LIMITS: same bull-only 2013-2018 sample (no 2020/2022); regime
//  filter stayed ON in every test; win-rate objectives inherently favor
//  scalp geometry - do not read 83% win as 83%-of-a-big-R. Re-verify in
//  TradingView's own tester.
// ---- CHANGELOG v4 ----------------------------------------------------------
//  Default-settings behavior is IDENTICAL to v3 (the backtested config).
//  Fixes only bite in non-default modes; new features default OFF.
//  FIXES:
//  * Cooldown now triggers only after a LOSING exit, as its label always
//    claimed. v3 set the cooldown clock on EVERY flat - a target hit or time
//    exit blocked the next entry too. Toggle back with "Cooldown only after
//    a losing exit" = off.
//  * Stop-entry invalidation: in "Stop (enter the bounce)" mode a pending
//    entry is now cancelled if price breaks the setup's stop level first -
//    v3 would happily fill you into an already-broken structure. Limit mode
//    is untouched (a limit at 0.382 always fills before the stop can trade).
//  * tgtFib is no longer a dead input while trailStop is on: the trail's
//    final target is its own input (runnerFib, default 1.618 = old hardcode).
//  * Long/short setup math unified in one function (v3 had two hand-mirrored
//    ~45-line blocks - one source of truth, no more "fixed long, forgot short").
//  NEW (all default OFF or display-only):
//  * R-multiple stats in the table: expectancy (avg R), avg win R / avg loss R,
//    max losing streak - so the header's "+0.40R" style claims are verifiable
//    on-chart. (R uses the initial stop distance at fill; with pyramiding=0
//    and no reversals this is exact per position, incl. both partial legs.)
//  * Breakeven option: move the stop to the actual fill price after price
//    moves +N R in your favor (works with or without the fib trail).
//  * Regime SMA can now be computed on a higher timeframe (blank = chart TF
//    = v3 behavior). Uses lookahead_off - no repaint.
//  * Optional "move gone" cancel: drop a pending LIMIT entry once price tags
//    the target zone without filling you (untested vs the v3 evidence - OFF).
//  * Webhook-friendly JSON alert payloads (plain text remains the default).
//  * Live visuals: the active stop is plotted as a red step-line while in a
//    trade (you can watch the ratchet), the regime SMA is plotted faintly,
//    and the setup drawing now labels the stop too.
//  * Tooltips on every non-obvious input.
// ---- CHANGELOG v3 (offline backtest: 18 US large-caps across 10 sectors,
//      real daily OHLCV Feb-2013..Feb-2018, Python port of this exact logic) ----
//  EVIDENCE (10 dev tickers -> 8 untouched holdout tickers):
//    old defaults:            PF 0.62 / 0.70, avg -0.24R / -0.15R  (loses on both)
//    v3 defaults:             PF 2.61 / 1.69, avg +0.40R / +0.21R  (profits on both)
//  * Entry default = LIMIT. Pivots confirm `prd` bars late; a stop-entry then
//    fills ~market far past the fib level (worst single flaw found).
//  * entryFib default = 0.382 (0.318-0.5 all profitable; plateau center).
//    The old useRR gate was dead with the swing-buffer stop (RR is a constant
//    per fib level) - it filtered nothing and biased research to 0.236.
//  * useRR default = OFF (only meaningful with the ATR stop).
//  * Volume filter default = ON (anchor pivot >= 1.3x avg vol). Robust 1.15-1.5x.
//  * lockBracket default = ON: stops a new same-direction setup from
//    re-pointing an OPEN trade's bracket and un-ratcheting the trail.
//  * Shorts default = OFF: lost on ALL 18 tickers (bull-only sample - if you
//    trade shorts, gate them with the regime filter and test on bear data).
//  * Regime filter default = ON (longs only above 200SMA) - principled
//    protection for bear regimes the sample does NOT cover.
//  KNOWN LIMITS: ~180 trades for the chosen config; Python port approximates
//  TradingView's fill engine (conservative stop-first on ambiguous bars);
//  2013-2018 only. Re-verify in TradingView's own tester.
// ---- CHANGELOG v2: alerts, stats table, date filter, scale-out, ATR stop ----
// ---- CHANGELOG v1: entry-type toggle, opposite-order cancel, cooldown ------
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
strategy("Fib Strategy (visual) v4.1", overlay=true,
     initial_capital=10000, default_qty_type=strategy.percent_of_equity,
     default_qty_value=100, commission_type=strategy.commission.percent,
     commission_value=0.05, slippage=2, pyramiding=0,
     max_lines_count=500, max_labels_count=100)

// ---------------- inputs ----------------
prd      = input.int(5,      "Pivot Period", minval=2, tooltip="A pivot confirms `prd` bars after it prints. 5 = high-win profile (more, faster setups); 8 = the v3 expectancy profile.")
entryFib = input.float(0.55,  "Entry retracement level", minval=0.1, maxval=0.9, step=0.01, tooltip="0.55 = high-win profile (deep pullback, quick 0.786 target). 0.382 = the v3 expectancy profile (0.318-0.5 all profitable there).")
stopBuf  = input.float(0.8,   "Stop buffer (x range beyond anchor 0)", minval=0.0, step=0.01, tooltip="0.8 = high-win profile: a WIDE stop that only rare full breakdowns hit (~1 stop per 7 trades in test). 0.05 = the v3 expectancy profile. Risk-based sizing keeps a stop-out at ~riskPct either way.")
tgtFib   = input.float(0.786, "Target (fib units)", options=[0.618, 0.7, 0.786, 1.0, 1.272, 1.618], tooltip="Fixed-bracket target. 0.786 = high-win profile (quick partial retrace of the swing). 1.0 = the v3 expectancy profile. IGNORED while the trailing stop is ON - the trail uses its own runner target (Power group).")
useLong  = input.bool(true,   "Take longs")
useShort = input.bool(false,  "Take shorts", tooltip="Lost on all 18 test tickers, but the sample was bull-only - see header. Gate with the regime filter and test on bear data first.")
minRange = input.float(0.04,  "Min swing size (range/anchor0)", minval=0.0, step=0.01)
maxRange = input.float(1.50,  "Max swing size (range/anchor0)", minval=0.0, step=0.05)
entryWin = input.int(30,      "Bars to wait for an entry fill", minval=1)
maxHold  = input.int(80,      "Max bars to hold a position", minval=1)
showDraw = input.bool(true,   "Draw the latest setup (entry/stop/target)")
trailStop = input.bool(false, "Trailing stop (ratchet up the Fib levels to the runner target)", tooltip="OFF = high-win profile (fixed 0.786 target; trailing would turn quick winners into breakeven scratches). ON = the v3 expectancy profile (rides to 1.618).")

// ---- zig-zag of the swing structure the strategy reads ----
showZZ   = input.bool(true,        "Draw zig-zag of the pivots used", group="Zig-zag")
zzUpCol  = input.color(color.lime, "Rising leg (low -> high)", group="Zig-zag")
zzDnCol  = input.color(color.red,  "Falling leg (high -> low)", group="Zig-zag")
zzWidth  = input.int(2, "Zig-zag line width", minval=1, maxval=4, group="Zig-zag")

// ---- "smarter" controls ----
useRisk   = input.bool(true,  "Risk-based sizing (size by stop distance, not 100% equity)", group="Smart")
riskPct   = input.float(1.0,  "Risk % of equity per trade", minval=0.1, maxval=5.0, step=0.1, group="Smart")
maxExpo   = input.float(100,  "Max position size (% of equity, no-leverage cap)", group="Smart")
// Entry order TYPE. A pivot confirms `prd` bars late, so by order-placement time
// price is often already past the level: a Stop then fills ~market (you pay up).
// Limit instead waits for price to trade back DOWN/UP to the level.
entryType = input.string("Limit (wait for the pullback)", "Entry order type", options=["Stop (enter the bounce)", "Limit (wait for the pullback)"], group="Smart", tooltip="Limit was the single biggest edge in the v3 backtest. Note: risk-based sizing is exact for Limit fills; for Stop entries the real fill can be worse than the level, so sizing is approximate there.")
useCooldown = input.bool(false, "Cooldown after a stop-out (skip new entries for a few bars)", group="Smart")
coolBars  = input.int(10, "Cooldown length (bars)", minval=1, group="Smart")
coolLossOnly = input.bool(true, "Cooldown only after a losing exit", group="Smart", tooltip="ON = only losing trades start the cooldown clock (what the cooldown was always meant to do). OFF = v3 behavior: ANY exit - even a target hit - blocks the next entry.")
lockBracket = input.bool(true, "Lock stop/target at entry (ignore new setups while in a trade)", group="Smart")
useLimit  = entryType == "Limit (wait for the pullback)"
stopInvalidate = input.bool(true, "Cancel pending STOP entry if the stop level trades first", group="Smart", tooltip="Only relevant in Stop entry mode. If price breaks the setup's stop level while the entry is still pending, the structure is broken - v3 would still take the fill. Limit mode is unaffected (a limit fills before the stop can be reached).")
cancelAtTgt = input.bool(false, "Cancel pending LIMIT entry once price tags the target first", group="Smart", tooltip="If the move completes (target zone reached) before the pullback ever fills you, the edge is spent - skip the late fill on the way back down. OFF by default: not part of the v3 backtest evidence.")
// NOTE: with the swing-buffer stop, RR is a constant -> this gate is only
// meaningful when the ATR stop is enabled. Off by default.
useRR     = input.bool(false, "Require minimum reward:risk (only meaningful with ATR stop)", group="Smart")
minRR     = input.float(1.5,  "Min reward:risk (target vs stop)", minval=0.5, step=0.1, group="Smart")
useRegime = input.bool(true,  "Regime filter (longs only above SMA, shorts only below)", group="Smart")
regimeLen = input.int(200,    "Regime SMA length", minval=20, group="Smart")
regimeTf  = input.timeframe("", "Regime timeframe (blank = chart)", group="Smart", tooltip="Compute the regime SMA on a higher timeframe (e.g. W on a daily chart). Uses lookahead_off - no repaint; the HTF value lags by one HTF bar, as it would live.")
showRegime = input.bool(true, "Plot the regime SMA", group="Smart")
useAngle = input.bool(false, "Require steep '45-deg' impulse into entry", group="Smart")
minAngle = input.float(0.3,  "Min impulse slope (ATR per bar from anchor)", minval=0.0, step=0.05, group="Smart")
atrA     = ta.atr(14)

// ---- POWER: exits, stops, alerts ----
usePartial = input.bool(false, "Scale out: partial at target, runner trails to the runner target", group="Power")
partialPct = input.float(50,   "Partial size (% of position)", minval=10, maxval=90, step=5, group="Power")
runnerFib  = input.float(1.618, "Trail / runner final target (fib units)", options=[1.272, 1.618, 2.0, 2.618], group="Power", tooltip="Where the trailing stop's limit (and the scale-out runner) aims. 1.618 = the value v3 hard-coded and backtested.")
useAtrStop = input.bool(false, "ATR stop (x ATR from entry) instead of swing-buffer stop", group="Power")
atrStopMult = input.float(2.0, "ATR stop multiple", minval=0.5, step=0.25, group="Power")
useBE      = input.bool(false, "Move stop to breakeven after +N R", group="Power", tooltip="Once price moves N initial-risk units in your favor, ratchet the stop to the actual fill price. Stacks with the fib trail (whichever stop is tighter wins). Untested vs the v3 evidence - OFF by default.")
beTrig     = input.float(1.0,  "Breakeven trigger (R multiples)", minval=0.25, step=0.25, group="Power")
useAlerts  = input.bool(true,  "Fire alert() on setup / fill / partial / exit", group="Power")
alertJson  = input.bool(false, "JSON alert payloads (webhook-friendly)", group="Power", tooltip="Wrap every alert in a small JSON object (event, ticker, price, msg) so a webhook can parse it. OFF = v3 plain text.")

// ---- backtest window (for in-sample / OOS splits) ----
useDate = input.bool(false, "Limit signals to a date range", group="Backtest window")
startT  = input.time(timestamp("1 Jan 2015 00:00 +0000"), "Start", group="Backtest window")
endT    = input.time(timestamp("1 Jan 2035 00:00 +0000"), "End", group="Backtest window")
inRange = not useDate or (time >= startT and time <= endT)

// ---- stats table ----
showStats = input.bool(true, "Show performance stats table", group="Stats")

// ---- volume confirmation ----
useVol   = input.bool(false, "Require above-average volume at the anchor pivot", group="Volume", tooltip="OFF = high-win profile (the filter cut trade count without lifting the win rate in the 10-ticker test). ON at 1.3x = the v3 expectancy profile, where it helped.")
volLen   = input.int(20,     "Average-volume length", minval=5, group="Volume")
volMult  = input.float(1.3,  "Anchor volume must be >= this x average", minval=1.0, step=0.1, group="Volume")
shadeVol = input.bool(true,  "Highlight high-volume bars in blue", group="Volume")

// ---- auto 45-degree trend lines ----
show45   = input.bool(true,  "Draw auto 45-degree trend lines", group="45-degree line")
look45   = input.int(200,    "Lookback to anchor the high/low", minval=10, group="45-degree line")
slope45  = input.float(1.0,  "Steepness (1.0 = reach the opposite extreme at the current bar)", minval=0.1, step=0.25, group="45-degree line")
upCol45  = input.color(color.aqua,    "Rising line (from lowest low)", group="45-degree line")
dnCol45  = input.color(color.fuchsia, "Falling line (from highest high)", group="45-degree line")

// regime SMA - on the chart TF (blank input, v3 behavior) or a higher one.
// lookahead_off: on a HTF the last CONFIRMED HTF value is used - no repaint.
regimeSma = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, regimeTf, ta.sma(close, regimeLen), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
bullRegime = na(regimeSma) or close > regimeSma
bearRegime = na(regimeSma) or close < regimeSma

// risk-based qty: size so a stop-out loses ~riskPct of equity; cap at maxExpo.
// NB: for a Stop entry the actual fill can be worse than entryPx, so risk sizing
// is approximate in that mode; for a Limit entry the fill IS entryPx (exact).
qtyFor(float entryPx, float stopPx) =>
    dist = math.abs(entryPx - stopPx)
    riskQty = dist > 0 ? (strategy.equity * riskPct / 100) / dist : na
    capQty  = (strategy.equity * maxExpo / 100) / entryPx
    useRisk ? math.min(riskQty, capQty) : na

// one alert pipe: plain text (v3) or a JSON payload a webhook can parse
f_alert(string ev, string msg) =>
    if useAlerts
        payload = alertJson ? '{"event":"' + ev + '","ticker":"' + syminfo.ticker + '","price":' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + ',"msg":"' + msg + '"}' : msg
        alert(payload, alert.freq_once_per_bar)

// ---------------- pivots (confirmed prd bars back) -------------------------
ph = ta.pivothigh(high, prd, prd)
pl = ta.pivotlow(low,  prd, prd)
var float phPrice = na
var int   phBar   = na
var float plPrice = na
var int   plBar   = na
avgVol = ta.sma(volume, volLen)
pivRelVol = na(avgVol[prd]) or avgVol[prd] == 0 ? na : volume[prd] / avgVol[prd]
var float phVol = na
var float plVol = na
if not na(ph)
    phPrice := ph
    phBar   := bar_index - prd
    phVol   := pivRelVol
if not na(pl)
    plPrice := pl
    plBar   := bar_index - prd
    plVol   := pivRelVol

// ---- highlight HIGH-volume bars in blue ----
curRelVol = na(avgVol) or avgVol == 0 ? na : volume / avgVol
volTransp = math.max(0, math.min(85, 108 - curRelVol * 46))
isHiVol   = not na(curRelVol) and curRelVol >= 1
volBarCol = color.new(color.blue, volTransp)
barcolor(shadeVol and isHiVol ? volBarCol : na, title="Volume highlight")

// ---- zig-zag: connect the confirmed pivots into a swing line ----
var float zzP0 = na
var int   zzB0 = na
var float zzP1 = na
var int   zzB1 = na
var bool  zzH1 = na
var line  zzSeg = na
var line[] zzPerm = array.new_line()
if showZZ and not na(ph)
    bb = bar_index - prd
    if na(zzP1)
        zzP1 := ph
        zzB1 := bb
        zzH1 := true
    else if zzH1
        if ph > zzP1
            zzP1 := ph
            zzB1 := bb
            if not na(zzSeg)
                line.set_xy2(zzSeg, zzB1, zzP1)
    else
        if not na(zzSeg)
            array.push(zzPerm, zzSeg)
        zzP0 := zzP1
        zzB0 := zzB1
        zzP1 := ph
        zzB1 := bb
        zzH1 := true
        zzSeg := line.new(zzB0, zzP0, zzB1, zzP1, color=zzUpCol, width=zzWidth)
    if array.size(zzPerm) > 150
        line.delete(array.shift(zzPerm))
if showZZ and not na(pl)
    bb = bar_index - prd
    if na(zzP1)
        zzP1 := pl
        zzB1 := bb
        zzH1 := false
    else if not zzH1
        if pl < zzP1
            zzP1 := pl
            zzB1 := bb
            if not na(zzSeg)
                line.set_xy2(zzSeg, zzB1, zzP1)
    else
        if not na(zzSeg)
            array.push(zzPerm, zzSeg)
        zzP0 := zzP1
        zzB0 := zzB1
        zzP1 := pl
        zzB1 := bb
        zzH1 := false
        zzSeg := line.new(zzB0, zzP0, zzB1, zzP1, color=zzDnCol, width=zzWidth)
    if array.size(zzPerm) > 150
        line.delete(array.shift(zzPerm))

var int pendBar  = na
var int entryBar = na
var int lastExitBar = na   // bar of the most recent cooldown-relevant exit

// active-trade anchors for the trailing stop / breakeven / R accounting
var float tA0   = na
var float tRng  = na
var bool  tLong = na
var float curStop = na
var float tRiskPS = na     // initial risk per share of the CURRENT position (set at fill)

// drawing handles — only the latest setup is kept on screen
var box   bx  = na
var line  lnE = na
var line  lnS = na
var line  lnT = na
var line  lnSwing = na
var label lbE = na
var label lbS = na
var label lbT = na
var label lbH = na
var label lbL = na

// values for a setup detected on this bar (na = none)
float nE = na
float nS = na
float nT = na
float nA0 = na
float nA1 = na
bool  nLong = false
bool  newSetup = false

// ---- position transitions: cooldown clock + fill / partial / exit alerts ----
justFlat    = strategy.position_size == 0 and strategy.position_size[1] != 0
justOpened  = strategy.position_size != 0 and strategy.position_size[1] == 0
partialFill = strategy.position_size != 0 and strategy.position_size[1] != 0 and math.abs(strategy.position_size) < math.abs(strategy.position_size[1])
if justFlat
    lastPnL = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? strategy.closedtrades.profit(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : na
    if not coolLossOnly or (not na(lastPnL) and lastPnL < 0)
        lastExitBar := bar_index
    f_alert("flat", "Fib strategy FLAT on " + syminfo.ticker + " (position closed)")
if justOpened
    tRiskPS := math.abs(strategy.position_avg_price - curStop)
    f_alert("fill", "Fib entry FILLED on " + syminfo.ticker + " at ~" + str.tostring(strategy.position_avg_price, format.mintick) + (strategy.position_size > 0 ? " (long)" : " (short)"))
if partialFill
    f_alert("partial", "Fib PARTIAL target hit on " + syminfo.ticker + " - runner still on")
inCooldown = useCooldown and not na(lastExitBar) and (bar_index - lastExitBar) < coolBars

// ---- R-multiple accounting (feeds the stats table's expectancy rows) ----
// R = closed-trade profit / (shares x initial stop distance at fill). With
// pyramiding=0 and no reversals, every closed trade processed on a given bar
// belongs to the position whose tRiskPS is current - incl. both partial legs.
var int   procTrades   = 0
var float sumR         = 0.0
var int   rCount       = 0
var float sumWinR      = 0.0
var int   winRCount    = 0
var float sumLossR     = 0.0
var int   lossRCount   = 0
var int   curLossStrk  = 0
var int   maxLossStrk  = 0
if strategy.closedtrades > procTrades
    for i = procTrades to strategy.closedtrades - 1
        prof = strategy.closedtrades.profit(i)
        sz   = math.abs(strategy.closedtrades.size(i))
        r    = na(tRiskPS) or tRiskPS <= 0 or sz == 0 ? na : prof / (sz * tRiskPS)
        if not na(r)
            sumR   += r
            rCount += 1
            if r > 0
                sumWinR   += r
                winRCount += 1
                curLossStrk := 0
            else
                sumLossR    += r
                lossRCount  += 1
                curLossStrk += 1
                maxLossStrk := math.max(maxLossStrk, curLossStrk)
    procTrades := strategy.closedtrades

// ---------------- setup math: ONE source of truth for both sides -----------
// a0 = anchor pivot (fib 0), a1 = the opposite pivot (fib 1.0). For longs
// rng > 0, for shorts rng < 0 - every level below works unchanged in both
// directions because the sign of rng carries the direction.
f_setupCalc(bool isLong, float a0, float a1, int aBar, float aVol) =>
    rng   = a1 - a0
    e     = a0 + entryFib * rng
    s     = useAtrStop ? e + (isLong ? -1.0 : 1.0) * atrStopMult * atrA : a0 - stopBuf * rng
    t     = a0 + tgtFib * rng
    valid = not na(s) and (isLong ? e > s : s > e)
    rr    = valid ? math.abs(t - e) / math.abs(e - s) : 0.0
    ang   = (bar_index > aBar and atrA > 0) ? math.abs(close - a0) / (atrA * (bar_index - aBar)) : 0.0
    relSz = math.abs(rng) / a0
    sizeOk = relSz >= minRange and relSz <= maxRange
    rrOk   = not useRR or rr >= minRR
    regOk  = not useRegime or (isLong ? bullRegime : bearRegime)
    volOk  = not useVol or (not na(aVol) and aVol >= volMult)
    angOk  = not useAngle or ang >= minAngle
    gateOk = not inCooldown and (strategy.position_size == 0 or not lockBracket)
    ok = valid and inRange and sizeOk and rrOk and regOk and volOk and angOk and gateOk
    [ok, e, s, t, rng]

// place the entry + its bracket (partial keeps its ORIGINAL bracket; only the
// runner leg trails). Pure orders - state updates stay with the caller.
f_place(bool isLong, float e, float s, float t, float a0, float rng) =>
    id = isLong ? "L" : "S"
    q  = qtyFor(e, s)
    strategy.entry(id, isLong ? strategy.long : strategy.short, qty=q, stop=useLimit ? na : e, limit=useLimit ? e : na)
    runnerTgt = a0 + runnerFib * rng
    if usePartial
        strategy.exit(id + "x1", id, qty_percent=partialPct, stop=s, limit=t)
        strategy.exit(id + "x2", id, stop=s, limit=runnerTgt)
    else
        strategy.exit(id + "x", id, stop=s, limit=trailStop ? runnerTgt : t)

// ---------------- LONG setup: fresh low + a prior high above it -------------
if useLong and not na(pl) and not na(phPrice) and phBar < plBar and phPrice > plPrice
    [okL, eL, sL, tL, rngL] = f_setupCalc(true, plPrice, phPrice, plBar, plVol)
    if okL
        nE := eL
        nS := sL
        nT := tL
        nA0 := plPrice
        nA1 := phPrice
        nLong := true
        newSetup := true
        f_place(true, eL, sL, tL, plPrice, rngL)
        pendBar := bar_index
        tA0 := plPrice
        tRng := rngL
        tLong := true
        curStop := sL
        f_alert("setup", "Fib LONG setup on " + syminfo.ticker + ": entry " + str.tostring(nE, format.mintick) + ", stop " + str.tostring(nS, format.mintick) + ", target " + str.tostring(nT, format.mintick))

// ---------------- SHORT setup: fresh high + a prior low below it ------------
if useShort and not na(ph) and not na(plPrice) and plBar < phBar and plPrice < phPrice
    [okS, eS, sS, tS, rngS] = f_setupCalc(false, phPrice, plPrice, phBar, phVol)
    if okS
        nE := eS
        nS := sS
        nT := tS
        nA0 := phPrice
        nA1 := plPrice
        nLong := false
        newSetup := true
        f_place(false, eS, sS, tS, phPrice, rngS)
        pendBar := bar_index
        tA0 := phPrice
        tRng := rngS
        tLong := false
        curStop := sS
        f_alert("setup", "Fib SHORT setup on " + syminfo.ticker + ": entry " + str.tostring(nE, format.mintick) + ", stop " + str.tostring(nS, format.mintick) + ", target " + str.tostring(nT, format.mintick))

// ---- don't let a leftover opposite pending order flip an open position ----
if strategy.position_size > 0
    strategy.cancel("S")
if strategy.position_size < 0
    strategy.cancel("L")

// ---- pending-order hygiene (only while flat with a live entry order) ----
pendingFlat = not na(pendBar) and strategy.position_size == 0
// Stop-entry mode: the structure died before the entry triggered - stand down.
if pendingFlat and not useLimit and stopInvalidate and not na(curStop)
    if tLong ? low <= curStop : high >= curStop
        strategy.cancel(tLong ? "L" : "S")
        pendBar := na
        f_alert("cancel", "Fib setup INVALIDATED on " + syminfo.ticker + " - stop level traded before entry")
// Limit mode (optional): the move completed without the pullback - edge spent.
if pendingFlat and useLimit and cancelAtTgt and not na(tA0)
    if tLong ? high >= tA0 + tgtFib * tRng : low <= tA0 + tgtFib * tRng
        strategy.cancel(tLong ? "L" : "S")
        pendBar := na
        f_alert("cancel", "Fib setup EXPIRED on " + syminfo.ticker + " - target tagged before the pullback filled")

// ---- redraw: erase previous setup, draw the new one only ----
if newSetup and showDraw
    box.delete(bx)
    line.delete(lnE)
    line.delete(lnS)
    line.delete(lnT)
    line.delete(lnSwing)
    label.delete(lbE)
    label.delete(lbS)
    label.delete(lbT)
    label.delete(lbH)
    label.delete(lbL)
    rightX = bar_index + entryWin + maxHold
    c = nLong ? color.green : color.red
    bx  := box.new(bar_index, math.max(nA0, nA1), rightX, math.min(nA0, nA1),
             border_color=color.new(color.gray, 50), bgcolor=color.new(c, 90))
    lnE := line.new(bar_index, nE, rightX, nE, color=color.yellow, width=2)
    lnS := line.new(bar_index, nS, rightX, nS, color=color.red, width=1, style=line.style_dashed)
    lnT := line.new(bar_index, nT, rightX, nT, color=color.green, width=2)
    lbE := label.new(rightX, nE, "entry", style=label.style_label_left,
             color=color.new(color.yellow, 60), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    lbS := label.new(rightX, nS, "stop", style=label.style_label_left,
             color=color.new(color.red, 60), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    lbT := label.new(rightX, nT, "target", style=label.style_label_left,
             color=color.new(color.green, 60), textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)
    lnSwing := line.new(plBar, plPrice, phBar, phPrice,
             color=color.new(color.white, 20), style=line.style_dotted, width=2)
    hVolTxt = na(phVol) ? "" : "  " + str.tostring(phVol, "#.0") + "x vol"
    lVolTxt = na(plVol) ? "" : "  " + str.tostring(plVol, "#.0") + "x vol"
    lbH := label.new(phBar, phPrice, (nLong ? "● SWING HIGH (1.0)" : "● SWING HIGH (0)") + hVolTxt,
             style=label.style_label_down, color=color.orange,
             textcolor=color.black, size=size.small)
    lbL := label.new(plBar, plPrice, (nLong ? "● SWING LOW (0)" : "● SWING LOW (1.0)") + lVolTxt,
             style=label.style_label_up, color=color.blue,
             textcolor=color.white, size=size.small)

// ---- in-trade stop management: fib ratchet + breakeven, one re-issue point ----
if strategy.position_size != 0 and not na(tA0)
    be   = strategy.position_avg_price          // breakeven = actual fill price
    l618 = tA0 + 0.618 * tRng
    l100 = tA0 + 1.0   * tRng
    l127 = tA0 + 1.272 * tRng
    runnerTgt = tA0 + runnerFib * tRng
    fixedTgt  = tA0 + tgtFib   * tRng
    if trailStop
        if tLong
            curStop := high >= l127 ? math.max(curStop, l100) : high >= l100 ? math.max(curStop, l618) : high >= l618 ? math.max(curStop, be) : curStop
        else
            curStop := low <= l127 ? math.min(curStop, l100) : low <= l100 ? math.min(curStop, l618) : low <= l618 ? math.min(curStop, be) : curStop
    if useBE and not na(tRiskPS) and tRiskPS > 0
        if tLong and high >= be + beTrig * tRiskPS
            curStop := math.max(curStop, be)
        if not tLong and low <= be - beTrig * tRiskPS
            curStop := math.min(curStop, be)
    if trailStop or useBE
        tgtSingle = trailStop ? runnerTgt : fixedTgt
        if tLong
            if usePartial
                strategy.exit("Lx2", "L", stop=curStop, limit=runnerTgt)
            else
                strategy.exit("Lx", "L", stop=curStop, limit=tgtSingle)
        else
            if usePartial
                strategy.exit("Sx2", "S", stop=curStop, limit=runnerTgt)
            else
                strategy.exit("Sx", "S", stop=curStop, limit=tgtSingle)

// cancel stale pending entries
if not na(pendBar) and strategy.position_size == 0 and (bar_index - pendBar) > entryWin
    strategy.cancel("L")
    strategy.cancel("S")
    pendBar := na

// max-hold time exit
if strategy.position_size != 0 and na(entryBar)
    entryBar := bar_index
if strategy.position_size == 0
    entryBar := na
if not na(entryBar) and (bar_index - entryBar) >= maxHold
    strategy.close_all(comment="time")

// ---- live overlays: the ratcheting stop while in a trade + the regime SMA ----
plot(strategy.position_size != 0 ? curStop : na, "Active stop (live)",
     color=color.new(color.red, 0), style=plot.style_linebr, linewidth=2)
plot(showRegime and useRegime ? regimeSma : na, "Regime SMA",
     color=color.new(color.orange, 55), linewidth=1)

// ---- auto 45-degree trend lines = the DIAGONALS of the high-low box ----
var line up45 = na
var line dn45 = na
var label up45L = na
var label dn45L = na
if show45 and barstate.islast
    line.delete(up45)
    line.delete(dn45)
    label.delete(up45L)
    label.delete(dn45L)
    llp = ta.lowest(low, look45)
    llb = bar_index + ta.lowestbars(low, look45)      // lowestbars is <= 0 (bars back)
    hhp = ta.highest(high, look45)
    hhb = bar_index + ta.highestbars(high, look45)
    rng45 = slope45 * (hhp - llp)                      // vertical travel by the right edge
    up45 := line.new(llb, llp, bar_index, llp + rng45, color=upCol45, width=2, extend=extend.right)
    dn45 := line.new(hhb, hhp, bar_index, hhp - rng45, color=dnCol45, width=2, extend=extend.right)
    up45L := label.new(llb, llp, "45° up", style=label.style_label_up,
             color=color.new(upCol45, 30), textcolor=color.white, size=size.tiny)
    dn45L := label.new(hhb, hhp, "45° down", style=label.style_label_down,
             color=color.new(dnCol45, 30), textcolor=color.white, size=size.tiny)

// ---------------- legend ----------------
var table lg = table.new(position.top_right, 1, 4, border_width=1)
if barstate.islast
    table.cell(lg, 0, 0, "Fib Strategy v4.1", bgcolor=color.gray, text_color=color.white, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(lg, 0, 1, "yellow = entry", text_color=color.yellow, text_size=size.tiny)
    table.cell(lg, 0, 2, "green = target",  text_color=color.green,  text_size=size.tiny)
    table.cell(lg, 0, 3, "red = stop",      text_color=color.red,    text_size=size.tiny)

// ---------------- performance stats ----------------
var table st = table.new(position.bottom_right, 2, 10, border_width=1)
if showStats and barstate.islast
    winRate = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? 100.0 * strategy.wintrades / strategy.closedtrades : na
    pf      = strategy.grossloss > 0 ? strategy.grossprofit / strategy.grossloss : na
    netPct  = 100.0 * strategy.netprofit / strategy.initial_capital
    ddPct   = 100.0 * strategy.max_drawdown / strategy.initial_capital
    avgT    = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ? strategy.netprofit / strategy.closedtrades : na
    expR    = rCount > 0 ? sumR / rCount : na
    avgWinR  = winRCount  > 0 ? sumWinR  / winRCount  : na
    avgLossR = lossRCount > 0 ? sumLossR / lossRCount : na
    table.cell(st, 0, 0, "Stats", bgcolor=color.gray, text_color=color.white, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(st, 1, 0, "", bgcolor=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(st, 0, 1, "Closed trades", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 1, str.tostring(strategy.closedtrades), text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 0, 2, "Win rate", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 2, na(winRate) ? "-" : str.tostring(winRate, "#.#") + "%", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 0, 3, "Profit factor", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 3, na(pf) ? "-" : str.tostring(pf, "#.##"), text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 0, 4, "Net profit", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 4, str.tostring(netPct, "#.#") + "%", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=netPct >= 0 ? color.lime : color.red)
    table.cell(st, 0, 5, "Max DD (% of initial)", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 5, str.tostring(ddPct, "#.#") + "%", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.orange)
    table.cell(st, 0, 6, "Avg trade", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 6, na(avgT) ? "-" : "$" + str.tostring(avgT, "#.##"), text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 0, 7, "Expectancy (avg R)", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 7, na(expR) ? "-" : str.tostring(expR, "#.##") + "R", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=na(expR) or expR >= 0 ? color.lime : color.red)
    table.cell(st, 0, 8, "Avg win / loss (R)", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 8, (na(avgWinR) ? "-" : str.tostring(avgWinR, "#.##")) + " / " + (na(avgLossR) ? "-" : str.tostring(avgLossR, "#.##")), text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 0, 9, "Max losing streak", text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.white)
    table.cell(st, 1, 9, str.tostring(maxLossStrk), text_size=size.tiny, text_color=color.orange)
